colspan="4"Jupp Derwall 1986 WORLD CUP FINAL V ARGENTINA Section::::1986 World Cup Final v Argentina .
With the highest attendance ever at a FIFA World Cup final , West Germany faced Argentina in Mexico City .
Although the South Americans ' star player Diego Maradona was closely guarded by the German team , he assisted the decisive 3 - 2 scored by Jorge Burruchaga , ensuring his country 's second World Cup win .
Late during the match , three yellow cards were given to Argentinians for time wasting .
