WORLD CUP FINAL V ARGENTINA Section::::1990 World Cup
Final v Argentina .
For this re - match of the 1986 Final , Argentina played extremely defensively .
Defender Pedro Monzón became the first player ever to receive a red card in a World Cup final , only to be joined by teammate Gustavo Dezotti 22 minutes later .
Although West Germany was the dominating side with 23:1 shots , it is fitting that the rough match was decided by a penalty kick taken by Andreas Brehme .
